<item>
            <title>[LU-3827] sgpdd-survey reported ios failed but did not report any errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3827</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Messages like this were seen. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;total_size 41943040K rsz 1024 crg   320 thr  2560 write 152 failed read 121 failed 
total_size 41943040K rsz 1024 crg   320 thr  5120 write 295 failed read 205 failed 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Three was no sign of what caused the IOs to fail.  It is believed to be an out of memory situation no error time data was reported. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch to make the results parsing a little more verbose so it will be clearer in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
